snippet.textDisplay:
2019 was a surprisingly solid year all around in terms of the music that was released. With the end of the decade looming around the corner, I wanted to end this year on a good note with a solid list. So here are what I think are the

TOP 10 ALBUMS OF 2019

(this’ll also include the scores of which I gave each album)

10. Rammstein’s untitled seventh album (82/100)
9. Cuz I Love You - Lizzo (84/100)
8. Jesus Is King - Kanye West (85/100)
7. Fear Inoculum - Tool (87/100)
6. ZUU - Denzel Curry (87/100)
5. Fishing for Fishies - King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard (87/100)
4. IGOR - Tyler, The Creator (89/100)
3. Infest the Rats’ Nest - King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard (90/100)
2. Trust in the Lifeforce of the Deep Mystery - The Comet is Coming (91/100)
1. Titanic Rising - Weyes Blood (99/100)

If y’all have any questions or opinions about this list, feel free to comment, and I’ll gladly respond.

snippet.textDisplay:
WeakIish top 10 but the good ones in it are damn good. That being said, what I found weak for example...


Caligula is a strong project for its own reasons but was it a top 10 album across all the albums you reviewed this year? I don't know. It's different, jarring, honest sure...but that effect wears off after the third or fourth listen...Even then, it's only hailed as being so abbrasive by those who don't venture much into the extreme music landscape. Plecto Aliquien Capite vocally out performs it for many of the reasons critics hold the record so highly and sonically it's not sharper than anything you would find in the neighborhood of tettragrammacide.


Also, no Blood Incantation - Hidden History of the Human Race ? Even if it isn't on the list, hope you had a chance to enjoy that beast of a project.
